      },
      "date": "2013-08-27 22:06:37.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 7: Looks good to me, approved\n\n(1 inline comment)\n\n> Andreas Dilger wrote on patch #6:\n> > the return code for wait_event_interruptible() is ignored -\n> > what are the implications of this?\n>\n> James Simmons replied:\n> \n> The older code behaved this way also. The only error you\n> get back is -ERESTARTSYS if a signal is sent which in\n> that case it aborts the wait . Do we want to retry?\n\nI suspect that this error should be passed up the stack and the application should retry if it cares. Patrick Farrell  was just working on a similar problem and is CC'd in case he has some useful insight. See http://review.whamcloud.com/7002 for a related issue.  Any change w.r.t. this behaviour should be addressed in a separate patch, possibly under LU-3581.",
